WEBVTT

00:02.419 --> 00:04.159
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

00:14.597 --> 00:16.929
[PANTING]

00:21.062 --> 00:23.724
[MUSIC BOX PLAYING TCHAIKOVSKY'S
"DANCE OF THE SUGAR PLUM FAIRY"]

00:27.736 --> 00:28.942
[FLOOR CREAKING]

00:29.112 --> 00:30.943
[MUSIC STOPS]

00:33.450 --> 00:35.281
[CLOCKS CHIMING]

01:02.479 --> 01:04.515
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

01:41.976 --> 01:45.184
No, no, no. Help me.

01:45.355 --> 01:47.767
[MUSIC BOX PLAYING SOFTLY]

01:51.820 --> 01:53.902
GIRL:
No!

01:54.072 --> 01:55.687
[GASPS]

01:56.366 --> 01:58.527
[PANTING]

02:02.580 --> 02:05.538
[MUSIC BOX PLAYING IN DISTANCE]

02:10.547 --> 02:12.458
[MUSIC BOX PLAYING NEARBY]

03:56.110 --> 03:58.977
If you'd admit you moved in,
you wouldn't have to sneak down...

03:59.155 --> 04:01.191
...in the middle of the night and unpack.

04:01.366 --> 04:02.822
Well, they're not my things.

04:02.992 --> 04:06.155
I mean, they are my things, technically.

04:06.329 --> 04:07.364
What is it?

04:07.538 --> 04:08.994
[LOIS SIGHS]

04:10.208 --> 04:13.120
Something I've been avoiding
for 15 years.

04:18.675 --> 04:21.166
The general sent it after he left.

04:21.344 --> 04:24.836
It's been in the back of my closet
growing up. I've never opened it.

04:25.723 --> 04:30.558
It's the keepsakes my mom gave me
after she found out she had cancer.

04:31.187 --> 04:34.679
Oh, my God, it's Old Blue.

04:39.195 --> 04:41.231
Mom used to keep it
in her kitchen window.

04:41.406 --> 04:43.522
I haven't seen it since sh--

04:47.662 --> 04:51.154
I never went to visit her
in the hospital, Clark.

04:52.875 --> 04:56.709
What kind of kid refuses to visit
their sick mom?

04:58.298 --> 05:00.459
A really scared one.

05:00.633 --> 05:03.750
She was there for ﬁve weeks...

05:06.431 --> 05:08.046
...and I didn't--

05:08.224 --> 05:10.556
I didn't say goodbye to her.

05:17.900 --> 05:20.312
But it looks like she did.

05:23.823 --> 05:26.064
This is from the hospital.

05:27.702 --> 05:33.447
Clark, what if she's angry
that I didn't go see her, you know?

05:33.624 --> 05:36.991
l'm-- I'm not sure I can face this.

05:39.714 --> 05:43.332
Lois, you shouldn't feel guilty
for not wanting to open up old wounds.

05:45.970 --> 05:49.007
Haven't you felt like something
is missing in your life...

05:49.223 --> 05:51.305
...since you cut ties with your dad?

05:53.102 --> 05:56.185
Well, Jor-El really isn't my dad.

05:56.689 --> 05:59.431
He's a machine. It's different.

06:00.234 --> 06:03.021
He sent you all the way here.

06:03.237 --> 06:06.149
He created an ice house,
and he trained you.

06:06.324 --> 06:10.237
He wouldn't do all of those things
if he didn't care about you.

06:10.995 --> 06:13.236
Look, if I'm up,
I really should be on patrol.

06:21.881 --> 06:24.247
I can stay if you need me to.

06:26.052 --> 06:28.008
It's okay, Clark.

06:57.667 --> 07:00.750
Tess, you said you needed help.

07:00.920 --> 07:03.252
I thought you meant Watchtower,
not scrapbooking.

07:03.423 --> 07:06.836
Clark, I meant when we came into work
tomorrow morning.

07:07.718 --> 07:09.219
Well, since I'm here....

07:10.596 --> 07:15.010
Someone broke into the mansion
and left this with a gift tag.

07:15.184 --> 07:17.391
It said "Happy Birthday, Tess."

07:18.938 --> 07:21.020
It's not my birthday.

07:21.190 --> 07:23.932
Someone's messing with me, Clark.

07:24.402 --> 07:26.859
And I had this nightmare
where l was a little girl...

07:27.029 --> 07:30.066
...and l was holding this exact music box.

07:30.700 --> 07:33.863
And then I woke up
and I found it in the library.

07:34.036 --> 07:35.947
[PLAYING "DANCE
OF THE SUGAR PLUM FAIRY"]

07:36.706 --> 07:37.991
[MUSIC STOPS]

07:42.128 --> 07:46.371
I thought that maybe I'd ﬁnd a picture of it
in this old photo album but....

07:48.718 --> 07:52.381
But this just reminds me of why
I don't like going home for Christmas.

08:03.232 --> 08:05.143
Tess, I may have found something.

08:17.663 --> 08:19.745
Does St. Louise's
mean anything to you?

08:19.957 --> 08:23.996
This might come as a surprise to you,
but I've never identiﬁed with any saints.

08:31.385 --> 08:32.591
Who is she?

08:33.179 --> 08:35.636
CLARK: This is the woman
who runs the orphanage.

08:35.806 --> 08:38.934
She's like the Mother Teresa
for needy children.

08:39.101 --> 08:41.592
They call her Granny Goodness.

08:46.442 --> 08:49.479
GRANNY:
Try to relax, dear.

08:49.820 --> 08:56.487
You just trust Granny
and you'll leave your past behind.

08:56.661 --> 08:59.118
But I don't wanna forget.

08:59.288 --> 09:04.624
Your memories
are just holding you back, my child.

09:04.794 --> 09:10.414
You may not see that now
but after we're done...

09:12.343 --> 09:14.800
...you'll thank me.

09:14.971 --> 09:16.586
[TESS GASPING]

09:18.599 --> 09:20.135
[SCREAMING]

09:57.305 --> 09:59.717
I hope I 'm doing this right.

10:00.516 --> 10:01.505
[SIGHS]

10:01.684 --> 10:03.424
Lois.

10:10.484 --> 10:12.770
My little girl.

10:12.987 --> 10:17.356
I've asked that you girls not be brought
to visit me at the hospital.

10:18.367 --> 10:21.609
I know you don't like being told
what to do...

10:21.871 --> 10:25.864
...but I want you to have
happy memories of me.

10:26.375 --> 10:27.410
Mom.

10:27.585 --> 10:31.498
The colonel is convinced
l'll pull through.

10:31.672 --> 10:37.383
He packed a bag
with my favorite nightgown and sweater.

10:38.262 --> 10:39.923
[CH UCKLES]

10:40.097 --> 10:42.634
I didn't know your father
noticed those things.

10:43.225 --> 10:46.388
He even managed to slip in Blue.

10:46.562 --> 10:51.807
Your father got this for me the day
we found out I was pregnant with you.

10:52.360 --> 10:58.947
We were stationed in Russia, and there,
this is considered a symbol of hope.

11:02.953 --> 11:06.411
He’s going to do
a wonderful job raising you.

11:06.999 --> 11:12.210
But sometimes,
girls need their mother.

11:14.298 --> 11:17.540
So as hard as these tapes are to make...

11:19.011 --> 11:23.596
...they're for the days
that I want to be there...

11:25.017 --> 11:27.099
...and won't be.

11:29.271 --> 11:35.107
Play the tapes. Think of me.

11:36.362 --> 11:41.197
Because losing a parent...

11:41.367 --> 11:45.076
...it can create a hole
in a person '8 heart.

11:47.081 --> 11:52.951
Someday, you're going to meet
someone special.

11:54.964 --> 12:01.176
And knowing you,
l'rn guessing tall, dark and handsome.

12:03.472 --> 12:06.464
And you can't commit
to that person fully...

12:06.684 --> 12:09.517
...if you think there's a love
that you're missing...

12:09.687 --> 12:12.850
...from some old memory.

12:14.525 --> 12:16.311
Like me.

12:19.029 --> 12:22.317
You can't let someone leaving you...

12:22.491 --> 12:26.029
...stop your future with someone else.

12:29.206 --> 12:30.662
[CH UCKLES]

12:34.503 --> 12:37.791
You know,
the thing about being a parent is...

12:40.217 --> 12:42.594
...it doesn't end.

12:45.264 --> 12:50.384
Not with age, not with death.

12:52.062 --> 12:56.305
I will always be your mother, Lois.

12:56.901 --> 13:01.611
And I will always love you.

13:26.555 --> 13:28.716
I swear I've never been here before.

13:28.891 --> 13:32.634
You may not remember, but that was you
standing on those steps 20 years ago.

13:32.812 --> 13:36.054
And someone broke into your house
to remind you of it.

13:43.489 --> 13:45.320
Hello.

13:45.491 --> 13:48.449
You must be the reporters who called.

13:48.619 --> 13:51.656
Welcome, welcome.

13:51.831 --> 13:55.198
The girls have been so excited,
they already feel like celebrities...

13:55.417 --> 13:59.956
...knowing that our humble little home
will be featured in the Daily Planet.

14:04.093 --> 14:09.429
GIRLS [SINGING]:
Amazing grace

14:09.598 --> 14:13.637
How sweet the sound

14:16.313 --> 14:19.430
[GIRL WHIMPERING]

14:20.234 --> 14:22.270
I left my notebook in the car.

14:24.446 --> 14:28.109
GIRLS:
[once was lost

14:30.786 --> 14:33.027
[GIRL WHIMPERING]

14:44.133 --> 14:47.671
-Are you all right?
-Hurry, before Granny comes back.

14:47.887 --> 14:49.002
Granny did this to you?

14:52.933 --> 14:55.720
My mom and dad just died
in a car crash.

14:55.895 --> 14:58.352
I can't lose my memories of them too.

14:58.564 --> 14:59.895
Let's go.

15:03.068 --> 15:05.229
[METAL CLATTERING]

15:07.448 --> 15:09.234
That's what Granny turns us into.

15:09.408 --> 15:11.490
Don't worry, I won't let that happen.

15:11.660 --> 15:14.493
Just wait in here.
I'll be right back for you.

15:15.915 --> 15:17.826
I'll be right back.

15:20.210 --> 15:22.462
[METAL CLANGING
AND WOMEN GRUNTING]

15:46.278 --> 15:47.518
I'm here to help you.

15:47.696 --> 15:49.357
[GRUNTS]

15:54.244 --> 15:58.738
No one here needs saving except you.

16:12.262 --> 16:17.097
You know, I've always been able to tell
an abandoned soul when I see one.

16:17.267 --> 16:19.428
It's a gift.

16:23.565 --> 16:25.396
Do the girls come here as babies?

16:25.567 --> 16:28.650
Unfortunately,
tragedy strikes as it pleases.

16:28.821 --> 16:31.028
They come at any age.

16:31.991 --> 16:36.701
It must be difﬁcult to ﬁnd
the older ones permanent homes.

16:36.870 --> 16:40.033
Truth is, by the time I get my hands
on the lost souls...

16:40.249 --> 16:45.789
...they no longer have that cute
baby scent childless couples yearn for.

16:45.963 --> 16:49.046
The children don't spend
their entire childhoods here, do they?

16:49.258 --> 16:54.673
Oh, mercy me,
you make it sound like punishment.

16:57.891 --> 17:02.976
I've been training my girls for decades,
not to blend into society...

17:03.147 --> 17:05.229
...but to conquer it.

17:05.399 --> 17:10.894
Here and around the world.

17:22.499 --> 17:26.833
My girls know
I'll always be here for them...

17:29.548 --> 17:32.711
...and I know they'll never desert me.

17:49.818 --> 17:52.935
I do hope you enjoyed
the birthday present.

17:53.530 --> 17:56.818
That music box brought such comfort
to you when you were young.

17:56.992 --> 18:01.076
I knew it would draw you back to me.

18:13.175 --> 18:14.961
[SHELBY WHIMPERS]

18:30.818 --> 18:33.025
Don't look at me like that.

18:33.904 --> 18:40.025
I just spent some quality time with my mom
and the light bulb ﬁnally turned on.

18:40.202 --> 18:43.365
Smallville and I can't move forward
until he deals with this hole...

18:43.539 --> 18:45.530
...his dad left in his heart.

18:46.625 --> 18:51.085
Come on, I am Watson to his Holmes,
Cher to his Sonny.

18:51.255 --> 18:53.416
Just like you're Scooby to his Shaggy.

18:55.384 --> 18:56.419
Fine, be that way.

18:56.593 --> 19:00.381
I'm still gonna try for a thaw in
the cold war between Clark and his dad.

19:37.092 --> 19:38.593
If this is the door...

19:40.137 --> 19:43.129
...where would Clark hide the key?

20:17.007 --> 20:19.544
No going back now.

20:24.097 --> 20:27.225
In my photo album, there are no photos
of me before I was 5.

20:27.392 --> 20:31.476
That's because
they didn't have you then. I did.

20:32.105 --> 20:35.518
That dream. That was a memory.

20:35.734 --> 20:38.146
You were chasing me.

20:38.820 --> 20:40.401
You were hurting me.

20:40.572 --> 20:43.530
GRANNY: My child, I could never hurt you.
I've always loved you.

20:43.742 --> 20:45.698
Stop it, and tell me the truth.

20:45.911 --> 20:48.618
Who am I? What happened to me?

20:48.830 --> 20:52.038
Do you think
I wanted to say goodbye to you?

20:52.251 --> 20:54.913
I was already training you.

20:55.087 --> 20:57.829
You had so much promise.

20:58.048 --> 21:02.963
Then your birth parents
found you a home, forced my hand.

21:03.136 --> 21:06.628
They wanted you sent far away,
told me to forget about you.

21:06.848 --> 21:08.930
My birth parents?

21:11.687 --> 21:15.350
-Who were they?
-They were powerful.

21:15.565 --> 21:17.851
They would've closed us down
if I'd fought back...

21:18.026 --> 21:24.363
...but I never stopped
watching over you.

21:25.575 --> 21:31.366
When I heard you were in that hospital,
I couldn't let you die.

21:31.540 --> 21:35.499
I had to save my dear girl.

21:35.711 --> 21:38.202
Cadmus Labs.

21:38.380 --> 21:39.711
You brought me there?

21:39.923 --> 21:41.959
The scientist did a remarkable job.

21:42.134 --> 21:45.672
You can't even see the scars.

21:55.063 --> 22:01.275
Abuse is a horrible cycle to break,
even for a strong woman.

22:01.445 --> 22:04.687
But nothing can break you.

22:05.198 --> 22:08.816
I've always known you were stronger
than any girl I'd ever chosen before.

22:08.994 --> 22:12.828
You've always been my favorite.
You see, I'm your true family.

22:13.749 --> 22:16.411
Why don't I remember?
Why don't I remember my real parents?

22:16.585 --> 22:18.041
You don't need to remember.

22:18.211 --> 22:20.247
Look at everything you've become
on your own.

22:20.422 --> 22:22.003
Why are you coming after me now?

22:22.174 --> 22:25.007
With your power,
we'll accomplish great things.

22:25.177 --> 22:29.420
And, my brilliant girl, very soon,
lines will be drawn.

22:30.432 --> 22:35.051
Believe me,
you'll be glad to have me on your side.

22:35.228 --> 22:37.935
Of course, it would've been better
if you'd come alone.

22:38.440 --> 22:41.557
But my girls will take care of your friend.

22:41.777 --> 22:45.440
Where is he?
What have you done to him?

22:47.032 --> 22:50.240
I've had quite enough of that behavior.

22:51.703 --> 22:54.115
[TESS GRUNTING]

23:11.306 --> 23:12.842
[PHONE CLATTERS]

23:38.208 --> 23:41.371
None of my girls ever leave me.

23:45.048 --> 23:46.549
I lost your broken soul once.

23:46.716 --> 23:50.129
Trust me,
I'm not going to let you go again.

23:50.595 --> 23:53.337
I have plans for you, Tess.

23:53.557 --> 23:57.675
You will be my most valuable soldier
in the coming war.

23:58.770 --> 24:03.389
Whether you want to be or not.

24:12.367 --> 24:13.482
Nighty-night.

24:13.660 --> 24:17.869
It's good to have you home,
back in your old room.

24:18.039 --> 24:19.825
[GRANNY LAUGHS]

24:40.103 --> 24:42.719
You don't have to do this.
I can get you out of here...

24:42.898 --> 24:45.230
...help your younger sisters
ﬁnd real homes.

24:46.151 --> 24:48.938
No one could ever love us
as much as Granny.

24:49.154 --> 24:51.770
She controls you. That's not love.

24:51.990 --> 24:53.946
She will never leave us.

24:54.117 --> 24:56.779
We'll never be lonely or afraid.

24:56.995 --> 24:59.281
Someone who loves you
doesn't make you forget...

24:59.456 --> 25:01.287
...who you are
and where you came from.

25:01.458 --> 25:04.074
This is our family now.

25:09.883 --> 25:12.920
And you don't know Granny
the way we do.

25:13.094 --> 25:16.222
Her power is absolute.

25:17.390 --> 25:21.099
And she is smarter than any human.

25:21.311 --> 25:24.269
Just as these green ﬁre rocks
temper our weapons...

25:24.481 --> 25:27.848
...making them stronger,
she makes us stronger.

25:28.026 --> 25:29.857
She's preparing.

25:30.028 --> 25:33.816
Soon, a great fury
will consume this world...

25:33.990 --> 25:37.323
...and no one will be able to stop us.

25:39.871 --> 25:41.407
GRANNY:
Harriet.

25:41.623 --> 25:46.834
I told you to look after our lost lamb,
not slaughter him.

25:47.003 --> 25:51.542
Take your sisters to their rooms
while I bring peace to our visitor.

25:58.723 --> 26:02.966
I don't care how powerful you are,
I won't let you ruin any more lives.

26:04.646 --> 26:07.513
You are in no position to stop me.

26:07.732 --> 26:10.724
Once I bury your memories...

26:11.278 --> 26:17.695
...you'll see life can be so much better
without a painful past.

26:50.775 --> 26:53.437
Move it or lose it, sister.

26:53.612 --> 26:55.352
[BOTH GRUNTING]

27:25.226 --> 27:27.888
Not exactly home sweet home.

27:29.731 --> 27:33.724
When Clark said you gave him
the cold shoulder, he wasn't kidding.

27:37.530 --> 27:42.365
Hello? Mr. El?

27:45.080 --> 27:48.789
I'm here to talk about your son, Clark.

27:49.417 --> 27:51.373
KaI-EI.

27:55.757 --> 28:00.751
Look, I know, as a parent, you had to make
the hardest decision ever...

28:01.346 --> 28:05.965
...to save your son
and send him here alone.

28:08.269 --> 28:12.638
When my mom was dying,
she tried to protect me too.

28:12.816 --> 28:15.853
And I love her, but she was wrong.

28:16.903 --> 28:19.690
I will never get to hold her again.

28:21.074 --> 28:25.659
But you, you can still be there for Clark.

28:25.829 --> 28:29.287
I mean, Kal-El.

28:31.459 --> 28:36.624
Your son needs a father
who believes in him.

28:39.300 --> 28:43.589
I wish knowing that I loved him
was enough.

28:46.516 --> 28:48.052
But Clark can't fully hear it...

28:48.226 --> 28:51.969
...with the ghost of your disappointment
haunting him.

28:52.147 --> 28:55.685
You're stopping him
from fulﬁlling his potential.

28:58.611 --> 29:01.068
He's an amazing man.

29:02.574 --> 29:04.860
He's a hero.

29:09.956 --> 29:11.696
Really?

29:12.917 --> 29:14.999
Nothing?

29:16.337 --> 29:19.374
You know, you may not care
about anybody else but yourself...

29:19.549 --> 29:21.335
...but Clark does.

29:21.509 --> 29:24.842
And you are not one-tenth
the Kryptonian he is.

29:27.515 --> 29:31.099
He is lucky to be rid of you.

29:47.202 --> 29:52.071
Don't fret, my child.
I'm here to ease your pain.

29:52.248 --> 29:56.207
-l have no pain.
-Oh, but you do.

29:56.377 --> 29:59.665
You are an abandoned soul.

30:00.215 --> 30:03.878
It's not your fault
your parents didn't want you.

30:04.052 --> 30:07.590
Let me help push all that anger away.

30:07.764 --> 30:09.049
You're way off.

30:09.224 --> 30:12.216
It's tempting, though, isn't it?

30:14.521 --> 30:16.102
No.

30:16.731 --> 30:18.847
Challenges are what make us
who we are.

30:19.859 --> 30:22.521
The people that I've lost,
the things that I've learned...

30:22.695 --> 30:24.435
...I wouldn't be the same
without them.

30:24.614 --> 30:27.777
We've all had moments we regret
and people who've let us down.

30:27.951 --> 30:31.535
I can take that all away.

30:33.373 --> 30:39.585
You just ask any of my girls,
I'm the most compassionate one of all.

30:57.605 --> 30:59.516
[G ROANS]

31:17.917 --> 31:21.284
[TESS GRUNTING]

31:27.719 --> 31:29.710
[WHIP CRACKING]

31:34.309 --> 31:36.095
[WOMAN GRUNTS]

31:45.653 --> 31:47.063
Thanks.

31:47.238 --> 31:52.699
I thought I could handle that on my own.
I'm so used to looking after myself.

31:52.911 --> 31:56.620
You're part of my team now.
I wasn't gonna abandon you.

32:21.356 --> 32:22.391
Lois.

32:23.733 --> 32:26.145
Jor-El, let her go.

32:26.527 --> 32:28.688
I may not have lived up
to your expectations...

32:28.863 --> 32:32.606
...but if you hurt her,
you would have failed all of mine.

32:35.495 --> 32:36.655
Lois, are you all right?

32:36.829 --> 32:39.366
Guess I need to work a little
on my dismount.

32:39.540 --> 32:42.828
Jor-El, he's here.

32:43.002 --> 32:45.618
Clark is here.
Come out, come out, wherever you are.

32:45.797 --> 32:47.913
Lois, he's not talking.

32:48.091 --> 32:50.707
I'm ﬁne with that.
After what he did to you, I'm done.

32:50.885 --> 32:53.217
No, wait.

32:53.388 --> 32:56.721
I love you too much to let you
and your father give up on each other.

32:56.891 --> 33:00.099
Just try one more time.

33:00.269 --> 33:02.225
Please.

33:06.734 --> 33:12.024
My son, I've only had the joy
of knowing you a few weeks.

33:12.323 --> 33:15.815
I wish I could be with you always,
to guide you and protect you.

33:15.994 --> 33:17.575
We don't have much time.

33:18.121 --> 33:22.831
LARA: My dearest Kai-El,
our love will always be with you.

33:23.001 --> 33:27.495
I can already see you carry within you
your father’s independent spirit.

33:27.672 --> 33:31.506
But more importantly,
your mother's never-ending bravery...

33:31.676 --> 33:34.292
...and her compassionate heart.

33:35.221 --> 33:38.384
Your father tells me the new world
you are journeying to, Earth...

33:38.558 --> 33:43.803
...is full of complicated beings
capable of great emotion.

33:43.980 --> 33:47.939
My wish is for you to live
a full and wonderful life.

33:48.151 --> 33:52.770
But I need you to know
you were born of a great love...

33:53.364 --> 33:57.482
...and your brilliant father has devised
a way for you to carry on that love...

33:57.660 --> 33:59.742
without us.

34:00.997 --> 34:04.581
The ship I designed
to carry you to your destiny...

34:04.751 --> 34:06.833
...can only hold one Kryptonian.

34:07.420 --> 34:13.336
One who has so much potential,
so unlike your father.

34:15.386 --> 34:17.342
Your mother and I cannot come with you.

34:17.930 --> 34:20.307
To do so would be to burden
your innocent soul...

34:20.475 --> 34:23.137
with our frailties and failures.

34:23.561 --> 34:27.395
But you have within you
the best of both of us...

34:27.565 --> 34:30.557
...and I am sending with you
all my knowledge...

34:30.735 --> 34:35.570
...but none of my ego or regrets.

34:35.740 --> 34:39.779
They will die with me here on Krypton.

34:41.704 --> 34:46.789
Whatever trials [put you through,
I will never lose faith in you.

34:46.959 --> 34:49.541
Quickly, before it's too late.

34:49.712 --> 34:52.203
We may not have been able
to save our planet-

34:52.423 --> 34:58.214
But we are conﬁdent
you will become Earth '8 greatest savior.

34:58.429 --> 35:02.013
And never doubt
that just as you are a part of us...

35:02.225 --> 35:05.342
...we will always be a part of you.

35:07.438 --> 35:09.520
Farewell, my son.

35:09.690 --> 35:11.271
Farewell.

35:42.265 --> 35:44.381
Hello, Granny.

35:44.642 --> 35:46.143
GRAN NY:
Desaad.

35:49.063 --> 35:51.520
DESAAD:
Ah, Godfrey.

35:51.732 --> 35:54.940
He has been chosen.

35:55.736 --> 36:01.197
Our dark lord has anointed him...

36:01.826 --> 36:05.739
...made him like us, a prophet.

36:09.000 --> 36:12.492
He is Darkseid's third minion.

36:14.463 --> 36:17.045
So I do have a higher purpose.

36:17.258 --> 36:19.715
Yes, Godfrey.

36:20.094 --> 36:22.961
Your golden voice
is broadcast around the world.

36:23.181 --> 36:24.546
Not impressed.

36:24.724 --> 36:27.557
And you,
I see you're enjoying your clubs.

36:27.727 --> 36:30.264
They seem more popular than ever.

36:30.479 --> 36:33.721
Our unholy trinity is complete.

36:33.900 --> 36:38.109
I bind their bodies,
Godfrey breaks their spirit...

36:38.279 --> 36:42.773
...and you, my beloved friend,
you clear their minds...

36:42.992 --> 36:45.108
...preparing the way
for Lord Darkseid.

36:58.132 --> 37:00.043
CLARK:
Yes and no.

37:01.636 --> 37:05.299
Yes, I think your mother
is still watching over you...

37:05.473 --> 37:07.213
...and no, I don't think you're crazy.

37:09.018 --> 37:14.012
She didn't want me to see her because
she was afraid she would look weak.

37:16.442 --> 37:19.525
I think she felt like she had failed me
by leaving.

37:22.406 --> 37:24.818
Clark, she's the bravest person I know.

37:28.329 --> 37:31.992
Maybe our parents thought that their
mistakes would be some sort of...

37:32.166 --> 37:33.622
...burden on us.

37:35.002 --> 37:36.503
LOIS:
Hmm.

37:37.755 --> 37:40.292
I would have liked
to have said goodbye.

37:40.466 --> 37:42.252
I think I could have handled it.

37:42.468 --> 37:44.299
But maybe they couldn't.

37:44.470 --> 37:47.086
I used to think Jor-EI
was this strong, unshakable force.

37:47.265 --> 37:49.347
Kind of like I thought
I was supposed to be.

37:51.102 --> 37:55.596
I don't think he's the easiest guy to read,
being that he's an ice fortress and all.

37:57.942 --> 38:00.274
But there's part of him
that's very human.

38:01.862 --> 38:03.602
Yeah.

38:05.866 --> 38:08.824
He blames himself
for losing our home.

38:09.870 --> 38:13.579
All the weight I thought I had, he was
carrying something so much heavier.

38:13.791 --> 38:15.998
And he didn't want you
to carry it with him.

38:18.212 --> 38:20.794
I'm glad that you got to see him.

38:21.632 --> 38:23.293
And thank you for showing me that.

38:24.552 --> 38:26.543
Thank my mom.

38:28.306 --> 38:32.595
Oh, and, uh, you can thank her
for this too.

38:35.021 --> 38:37.057
Toothbrush.

38:37.231 --> 38:40.894
My toothbrush. I'm in.

38:41.694 --> 38:43.275
Why don't you let me take you out?

38:43.446 --> 38:45.482
It's power ballad night
at the Ace of Clubs.

38:45.656 --> 38:47.567
Clark Kent and karaoke.

38:47.742 --> 38:50.734
Isn't that one of the signs
of the apocalypse?

38:51.370 --> 38:53.577
CLARK:
I'll go get our coats.

39:13.934 --> 39:18.769
-Are you blushing?
-No, I'm just happy.

39:19.565 --> 39:24.776
But if we don't get there soon, someone
is gonna steal all the Whitesnake songs.

39:37.917 --> 39:41.705
Hurry up, Clark, it's gonna start soon.

39:43.756 --> 39:46.543
Sooner than you think, Lois.

39:47.635 --> 39:50.092
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

40:07.363 --> 40:09.228
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

40:49.113 --> 40:50.353
Daddy.

40:55.995 --> 40:58.862
Daddy, wait, don't leave me.

41:03.878 --> 41:06.369
Daddy, I love you.

41:13.888 --> 41:16.049
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

41:24.732 --> 41:26.893
Happy Birthday...

41:29.320 --> 41:31.356
...Lutessa.

42:19.203 --> 42:21.194
